The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a classical problem in computer science, the maximum coverage problem, which involves selecting a subset of sets to maximize their union. This problem is a well-studied topic in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the paper proposes a randomized approximation algorithm that uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces the notion of partial sublinear time algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and analyzes the inapproximability of the maximum coverage problem, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
